This paper discusses the development of data mining algorithms suitable for cloud computing platforms, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also introduces a benchmark specifically designed for measuring the performance of cloud computing middleware for data-intensive computing, which is related to Database Systems (cs.DB) and Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE). Additionally, the paper discusses the security implications of cloud computing, which falls under the category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning models in data mining, which is related to Machine Learning (cs.LG).
